Vice President Joe Biden spoke with Ukrainian President Viktor Yanukovych and strongly condemned the violence against civilians in Kyiv. He urged Yanukovych to immediately withdraw all security forces, including police, snipers, military, paramilitary units, and irregular forces. Biden also stated that the United States is prepared to impose sanctions on officials responsible for the violence. He called on Yanukovych to take immediate and tangible steps to work with the opposition and address the legitimate aspirations of the Ukrainian people. Biden emphasized that the United States supports an independent and democratic Ukraine that follows the path chosen by its people.